🛠️ Core Maven Commands
mvn compile — Compile: Compiles the source code of the project.
mvn test — Run Tests: Runs the unit tests using a suitable testing framework (like JUnit).
mvn clean install — Build: Clears the target folder and builds the project, adding the resulting JAR/WAR to your local repository.
🔍 Specialized Build Commands
If you need more specific control over the build process:
mvn package — Generates the JAR/WAR file in the target directory without installing it to the local repo.
mvn clean — Deletes the target directory, ensuring your next build starts from scratch.
mvn test-compile — Compiles the test source code without running the tests.
mvn -DskipTests clean install — Builds the project while skipping the test execution phase.
